ider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaid%20non-client%20promotion%3A%20Affiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting-rating-methodology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20investing%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20composite%20image%20with%20a%20photo%20of%20Jackie%20Lam%20in%20front%20of%20a%20truck%20on%20the%20left%20and%20a%20photo%20of%20Daniel%20Masuda%20Lehrman%20on%20the%20right.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664bae2320abc1efe8fbc382%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Jackie%20Lam%20(right)%2C%20and%20Daniel%20Masuda%20Lehrman.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Masuda%20Lehrman%2C%20Jackie%20Lam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E10%25%20of%20Asian%20Americans%20live%20below%20the%20poverty%20line.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECFP%20Daniel%20Masuda%20Lehrman%20says%20the%20two%20biggest%20contributors%20to%20poverty%20are%20housing%20and%20cars.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELenders%20are%20often%20able%20to%20make%20debt%20more%20manageable%2C%20and%20balance%20transfer%20credit%20cards%20can%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMay%20is%20Asian%20American%20and%20Pacific%20Islander%20Heritage%20Month%2C%20and%20while%20there%20are%20certainly%20a%20lot%20of%20accomplishments%20and%20milestones%20that%20AAPI%20people%20can%20be%20proud%20of%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20Asians%20in%20America%20aren't%20all%20equally%20successful.%20As%20someone%20who%20identifies%20as%20Vietnamese-American%2C%20I%20can%20attest%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20are%20not%20a%20monolith.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2022%2F05%2Faanhpi-population-diverse-geographically-dispersed.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbout%2019.9%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20identify%20as%20being%20Asian%20in%20the%20U.S%2C%20which%20includes%2021%20distinct%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F03%2F27%2Fkey-facts-about-asian-americans-living-in-poverty%2F%23%5C%22%3EA%20recent%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20reveals%20that%2010%25%20of%20Asian%20Americans%20(2.3%20million)%20live%20below%20the%20poverty%20line.%20Poverty%20rates%20vary%20by%20group%20%E2%80%94%20only%206%25%20of%20Asians%20who%20identify%20as%20Indian%20are%20living%20in%20poverty%2C%20while%20Mongolian%20(16%25)%2C%20Hmong%20(17%25)%2C%20and%20Burmese%20(19%25)%20groups%20experience%20higher%20rates%20of%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeventy-nine%20percent%20of%20impoverished%20Asian%20Americans%20have%20been%20hit%20with%20financial%20challenges%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20These%20financial%20struggles%20tend%20to%20come%20in%20clusters%20%E2%80%94%20per%20Pew%2C%2065%25%20experienced%20at%20least%20two%20money%20troubles%2C%20such%20as%20having%20trouble%20paying%20bills%2C%20rent%2C%20or%20mortgage%3B%20losing%20their%20health%20insurance%3B%20not%20being%20able%20to%20save%20for%20emergencies%3B%20and%20needing%20to%20get%20food%20from%20a%20charitable%20organization%20or%20food%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20happens%20when%20you're%20hit%20with%20a%20flurry%20of%20financial%20hardships%3F%20I%20spoke%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcfp%5C%22%3Ecertified%20financial%20planner%3C%2Fa%3E%20Daniel%20Masuda%20Lehrman%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.masudalehrman.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMasuda%20Lehrman%20Wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Honolulu%2C%20Hawaii-based%20financial%20planning%20firm%2C%20on%20how%20Asians%20living%20in%20poverty%20can%20handle%20several%20money%20challenges%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Cut%20back%20on%20housing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20a%20higher%20number%20of%20AAPI%20households%20are%20multigenerational%20compared%20to%20other%20ethnic%20and%20racial%20groups%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20consider%20moving%20back%20with%20your%20family.%20That's%20because%20housing%20is%20usually%20the%20biggest%20expense%20in%20your%20budget%2C%20says%20Masuda%20Lehrman%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20multigenerational%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20not%20in%20a%20place%20to%20move%20in%20with%20your%20family%20or%20maybe%20you%20just%20don't%20want%20to%2C%20consider%20cutting%20back%20on%20your%20housing%20costs%20by%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20cheaper%20place%20or%20get%20roommates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Lower%20your%20car%20costs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20ways%20you%20can%20cut%20back%20on%20essential%20spending%20are%20to%20cut%20costs%20in%20the%20other%20two%20major%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20transportation%20and%20food.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20car%20loan%2C%20see%20if%20you%20can%20lower%20your%20car%20loan%20payment%20by%20selling%20your%20car%20and%20getting%20a%20cheaper%20used%20set%20of%20wheels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20get%20too%20much%20by%20getting%20a%20vehicle%20that%20they%20cannot%20afford%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BA%20low-hanging%20fruit%20way%20to%20save%20is%20to%20consider%20cutting%20back%20on%20your%20car%20expenses.%20It's%20really%20those%20big%20items%20that%20really%20make%20a%20difference%20%E2%80%94%20housing%20and%20your%20car.%20If%20you're%20not%20making%20smart%20decisions%20in%20those%20two%20categories%2C%20focus%20on%20them%20first.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Reach%20out%20to%20your%20lenders%20to%20better%20manage%20your%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EContact%20your%20lenders%20and%20creditors%2C%20explain%20your%20situation%20and%20see%20what%20they%20can%20do%20for%20you%20to%20help%20you%20manage%20your%20debt.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20will%20assume%20that%20they%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20help%20you%20out%20in%20any%20way%2C%20and%20so%20they%20don't%20even%20bother%20contacting%20their%20lender%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Masuda%20Lehrman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCommunicate%20with%20them%2C%20let%20them%20know%20that%20you're%20in%20a%20tough%20position%2C%20and%20ask%20what%20options%20are%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Masuda%20Lehrman.%20For%20student%20loans%2C%20there's%20deferment%2C%20which%20pauses%20your%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-private-student-loans%5C%22%3Estudent%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20up%20to%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20see%20what%20hardship%20options%20the%20card%20issuer%20offers.%20For%20instance%2C%20they%20might%20be%20able%20to%20lower%20your%20minimum%20monthly%20payment%2C%20temporarily%20pause%20your%20payments%2C%20or%20reduce%20your%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Consider%20a%20credit%20card%20balance%20transfer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECredit%20card%20debt%20is%20expensive.%20If%20you're%20struggling%20financially%20and%20have%20looming%20debt%2C%20you%20could%20transfer%20it%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-balance-transfer-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ebalance%20transfer%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%200%25%20introductory%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCredit%20cards%20might%20have%2020%25%20to%2025%25%20interest%2C%20so%20you%20cannot%20let%20credit%20card%20debt%20get%20out%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Masuda%20Lehrman.%20If%20that%20debt%20is%20going%20to%20bury%20you%2C%20applying%20for%20a%200%25%20APR%20credit%20card%20with%20a%20balance%20transfer%20means%20you%20won't%20have%20to%20pay%20interest%20for%20awhile%20%E2%80%94%20often%20up%20to%2018%20months.%20%26quot%3BThat%20gives%20you%20some%20wiggle%20room%20to%20get%20back%20on%20your%20feet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Avoid%20taking%20on%20more%20high-interest%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20possible%2C%20avoid%20taking%20on%20additional%20high-interest%20debt%2C%20suggests%20Masuda%20Lehrman.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20slippery%20slope%20when%20you're%20already%20in%20a%20tough%20spot%2C%20but%20if%20possible%2C%20avoid%20those%20crazy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-payday-loan%5C%22%3Epayday%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20even%20adding%20more%20to%20your%20credit%20card%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20due%20to%20the%20power%20of%20compound%20interest.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20same%20reason%20why%20people%20advise%20investing%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BAs%20they%20say%2C%20'%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3ECompounding%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20eighth%20wonder%20in%20the%20world%2C'%20because%20it%20%5Bgrows%5D%20at%20an%20exponential%20curve.%20It%20works%20the%20opposite%20way%20when%20you're%20taking%20on%20debt%20at%20a%2020%25%20or%2025%25%20interest%20rate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20y