ith%20dietary%20changes%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20a%20five-bean%20chili%20when%20you%20normally%20don't%20eat%20beans%2C%20or%20a%20whole%20new%20regime%20on%20January%201%2C%20Bulsiewicz%20said.%20They%20often%20feel%20sick%20within%20a%20few%20hours%20because%20they%20exceeded%20the%20capability%20of%20their%20gut%20microbiome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20lead%20to%20gas%2C%20bloating%2C%20abdominal%20discomfort%2C%20cramps%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20or%20constipation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20eat%20more%20fiber%2C%20he%20recommends%20starting%20low%20and%20going%20slow.%20Anytime%20we%20change%20our%20diet%2C%20our%20gut%20microbes%20are%20forced%20to%20adapt%2C%20he%20said.%20It's%20best%20to%20introduce%20new%20foods%20over%20time%2C%20starting%20with%20small%20amounts%20and%20gradually%20increasing%20portion%20sizes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20gut%20microbes%20come%20along%20for%20the%20ride%20and%20have%20time%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20change%20you're%20making%20in%20your%20diet.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20introduce%20the%20fiber%20and%20match%20it%20to%20the%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a02538e-622f-4dbb-9751-09dad8643e9c%5C%22%3EStay%20hydrated%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20well-hydrated%20improves%20our%20ability%20to%20process%20and%20digest%20fiber%2C%20Bulsiewicz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20fiber%20absorbs%20enough%20water%2C%20it%20creates%20soft%2C%20bulky%20poop%2C%20which%20is%20easy%20to%20pass%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fhealthy-lifestyle%2Fnutrition-and-healthy-eating%2Fin-depth%2Ffiber%2Fart-20043983%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIncrease%2520fiber%2520in%2520your%2520diet%2Cyour%2520stool%2520soft%2520and%2520bulky.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMayo%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Drinking%20water%20when%20you%20eat%20fiber%20also%20helps%20prevent%20gas%20and%20bloating%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.umassmed.edu%2Fnutrition%2Fblog%2Fblog-posts%2F2022%2F3%2Fso-you-want-to-increase-your-fiber-intake%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUMass%20Chan%20Medical%20School%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBulsiewicz%20starts%20each%20day%20with%20two%20glasses%20of%20water%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20drink%20two%20more%20glasses%20with%20each%20meal%20to%20ensure%20he%20stays%20hydrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrinks%20like%20coffee%2C%20tea%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-healthy-is-iced-coffee-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaffeinated%2C%20sugary%20%3C%2Fa%3Estuff%20are%20often%20dehydrating%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20fundamental%20idea%20of%20getting%20back%20to%20more%20water%2C%20and%20that%20is%20just%20good%2C%20healthy%20hydration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1852f58-91b6-49b2-a4b4-62049e1a9f66%5C%22%3ECheck%20it's%20not%20a%20chronic%20health%20issue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOftentimes%20gut%20symptoms%20can%20be%20a%20result%20of%20making%20radical%20changes%20too%20quickly.%20But%20they%20can%20also%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20chronic%20health%20issues%20such%20as%20Crohn's%20disease%20or%20Ulcerative%20colitis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20issues%20aren't%20always%20caused%20by%20the%20microbiome%2C%20although%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20story%2C%20Bulsiewicz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20can%20get%20bloating%20or%20diarrhea%20if%20they%20have%20a%20bad%20meal%2C%20but%20it's%20classed%20as%20a%20chronic%20issue%20when%20it%20becomes%20a%20pattern%20that%20affects%20your%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20is%20the%20case%2C%20don't%20just%20try%20to%20treat%20it%20yourself%2C%20he%20said.%20See%20a%20medical%20professional%20who%20can%20investigate%20what's%20causing%20the%20symptoms%20and%20make%20a%20diagnosis%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgi-doctor-sha